<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-52-1033 </DOCNO><TEXT>Four illustrated chapters deal with the following subjects: the energycontroversy (from the point of view of the environmental movement, energypolicy according to the demands of the public); renewable energy sources(decentralized power supplies, wind power, bioconversion); the sun shinesfor everybody (solar heating systems, solar architecture, heat pumps,solar cells); future prospects (commercial solar energy utilization,climatic changes in the past, present and future, general bibliography).A comparative evaluation of all energy sources available shows solarenergy to be the most environmentally compatible and, in the long term,most economic one. (HWJ).</TEXT></DOC>